-- Turkey to Buy Two Lockheed F-35 Jets, 15 Textron Helicopters
-- B y   A l i   B e r a t   M e r i c   a n d   E m r e   P e k e r
-- 2012-01-05T14:46:37Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-05/turkey-to-buy-two-lockheed-f-35-jets-15-textron-helicopters-1-.html
Turkey will purchase two  Lockheed
Martin Corp. (LMT)  F-35 fighter jets and and 15 helicopters from
 Textron Inc. (TXT)  for the police department, the Defense Industries
Undersecretary said today in a statement.  Prime Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan convened a meeting with
the Defense Industries Undersecretary Murad Bayar, Defense
Minister Ismet Yilmaz and the militaryâ€™s Chief of General Staff
Necdet Ozel today in Ankara, where the orders were approved.  Turkey also decided to start talks with Tusas Turkish
Aerospace Industries for the Ankara-based company to start mass
production of drones to meet an order of 10 domestically
manufactured unmanned aerial vehicles.  The government said it will open negotiations for an
agreement with Aselsan Elektronik Sanayi & Ticaret AS to develop
a multi-purpose radar for the navy, according to the statement.
Turkey said it picked Kale Havacilik Sanayi AS to build turbo-
 jet engines  in line with air force needs.  To contact the reporters on this story:
